  "response": "For international undergraduate students without housing concerns, several scholarship types are available:\n\n1. Merit-based Scholarships\n- Academic performance scholarships\n- High GPA and test score awards\n- Specific academic achievement recognition\n\n2. Country-specific Scholarships\n- Government-sponsored programs\n- Bilateral educational exchange scholarships\n- Regional cooperation scholarships\n\n3. Need-based Scholarships\n- Financial need demonstration\n- Income-dependent awards\n- International student financial support\n\n4. Subject-specific Scholarships\n- STEM field scholarships\n- Engineering and technology awards\n- Science and research-focused funding\n\n5. Athletic Scholarships\n- Sports performance scholarships\n- Athletic talent recognition\n- College team recruitment awards\n\n6. Diversity Scholarships\n- Minority student support\n- International student diversity programs\n- Cultural exchange funding\n\n7. Talent-based Scholarships\n- Art and music scholarships\n- Leadership potential awards\n- Exceptional skill recognition\n\n8. Corporate Scholarships\n- Company-sponsored international education support\n- Private sector educational funding\n- Specific industry-related awards\n\n9. Institution-specific Scholarships\n- University-funded international student programs\n- Institutional merit awards\n- Direct university scholarship offerings\n\nEach scholarship type has unique eligibility criteria and application requirements.",
